Method 1 — Install BIND9 on Offline Ubuntu/Debian Server (with Another Online Machine)
Step 1: On an online machine

Download all required BIND9 packages with dependencies:

sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install --download-only bind9 bind9utils bind9-dnsutils bind9-host bind9-doc dnsutils


This will download .deb files into:

/var/cache/apt/archives/


Copy them:

mkdir bind9-offline
cp /var/cache/apt/archives/*.deb bind9-offline/

Step 2: Transfer to the offline server

Use USB / SCP / ISO — whatever works.

scp -r bind9-offline/ root@offline-server:/root/

Step 3: Install locally on the offline server

On the offline machine:

cd /root/bind9-offline
sudo dpkg -i *.deb


If dependency errors appear:

sudo apt --fix-broken install --yes


(Don’t worry — it will use local .deb files, not the internet.)
